result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler J Moll was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Repeated Sexual Assault of Same Child (At Least 3 Violations of 1st Degree Sexual Assault), a class B felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.025(1)(d).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: If probation is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Conditions in all cases:  $518 costs on each case, to be paid during first 3 years of probation, review in 24 months, participate in AODA and sex offender treatment, no alcohol and illegal drug use. Participate in individual counseling with approved provider. Participate in psychological assessment and evaluation for medications and take medications as prescribed.  Participate in vocational services through DVR. If housing is able to be arranged at Pine Valley Residential Services, comply with all case management rules. Obtain GED. Defendant to have no contact with victims T.T. and H.T. Comply with sex offender registry.
